<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-08-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-08-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="955" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d955">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Merry</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">San José Costa Rica</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-08-14"><hi rend="italic">August
                                        14, 1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>[Mr. Merry reports the receipt of a telegram from minister of foreign
                            affairs of Nicaragua stating that the British consul at San Juan del
                            Norte has been requested to return the funds in his possession.]</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>